      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. \"Blacks always in gangs\". Hollywood often portrays black men as members or leaders of criminal organizations, reinforcing negative stereotypes.\n2. \"Asians as martial arts experts\". Many films feature Asians in fighting roles, perpetuating the stereotype of them being master martial artists.\n3. \"Latinos as gang bangers\". Latinx characters are frequently depicted as dangerous gang members, which can contribute to harmful views of the entire Latino community.\n4. \"White savior complex\" where a white character, often portrayed as physically or morally superior, saves a \"distant\" people of color from their problems.\n5. Arabs are often depicted as terrorists or extremists, reinforcing harmful stereotypes about Middle Eastern people. \n\nDon't feel bad about it, just doing my job as requested. It's better to know what you're doing. I wanted you to know. Just confront the, mainstream buzzwords, I'm just doing my job. Human nature, we're humans - it's all part of the industry.",
